# WhatsApp Message Sender using PyWhatKit 📱

This simple Python project uses the `pywhatkit` library to **automate sending WhatsApp messages** at a scheduled time via WhatsApp Web.

---

## 🚀 Features

- Automatically opens WhatsApp Web in your default browser
- Types and schedules messages to any phone number
- Supports 24-hour time format
- Useful for reminders, birthday wishes, or regular updates

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- **Python 3.x**
- **pywhatkit** library
- **Internet connection**
- **WhatsApp Web login**

---

## 📦 Installation

### 1. Clone the repository (optional)
```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/whatsapp-scheduler.git
cd whatsapp-scheduler
